<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/D_Traversal/public/directorystyle.css">
    <title>Website Security Report</title>
    <style>
        /* General Styles */
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #1f1f1f;
            color: #333;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            min-height: 100vh;
            overflow-y: auto; /* Enable scrolling for smaller screens */
        }

        .report-container {
            background-color: #292b2c;
            border-radius: 8px;
            padding: 20px;
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 600px;
            max-height: 90vh; /* Limit container height */
            box-shadow: 0px 0px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            overflow-y: auto; /* Enable scrolling within the container */
            color: #fff;
        }

        h2, h3, h4 {
            color: #ffffff;
        }

        p {
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: #ffffff;
        }

        ul.vulnerability-list {
            list-style-type: none;
            padding: 0;
        }

        ul.vulnerability-list li {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

        .back-button {
            display: inline-block;
            padding: 10px 15px;
            background-color: #ff7b57;
            color: #ffffff;
            text-decoration: none;
            border-radius: 4px;
            transition: background-color 0.3s ease;
        }

        .back-button:hover {
            background-color: #ff5722;
        }

        .note {
            background-color: #333;
            border-left: 4px solid #ff5722;
            padding: 10px;
            margin-top: 15px;
            color: #ffffff;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="report-container">
        <h2>Website Security Overview</h2>
        <p>This report highlights security issues found in the website and offers guidance on staying safe. Your security is our top priority, and we’re actively addressing these areas.</p>
        
        <h3>Identified Security Risks</h3>
        <ul class="vulnerability-list">
            <li>
                <h4>1. Directory Traversal Vulnerability</h4>
                <p><strong>Impact:</strong> Unauthorized users might gain access to sensitive information, risking data privacy.</p>
                <p><strong>How to Stay Safe:</strong> Avoid interacting with unfamiliar files or links, and report any suspicious activities immediately.</p>
                <p><strong>Our Solution:</strong> We’re implementing stricter file access controls and reinforcing validation checks to prevent unauthorized access.</p>
            </li>
            <!-- Additional vulnerabilities can be added here in the same format -->
        </ul>

        <h3>General Safety Recommendations</h3>
        <p>Follow these best practices to stay safe while using the website:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Use strong, unique passwords and avoid sharing them.</li>
            <li>Be cautious of links from unknown sources.</li>
            <li>Enable multi-factor authentication (MFA) for added security.</li>
            <li>Limit sharing sensitive information with unknown contacts.</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="note">
            <p><strong>Note:</strong> We are committed to regular security updates. If you notice any unusual activity, please contact our support team for assistance.</p>
        </div>

        <a href="/D_Traversal/index" class="back-button">Go Back</a>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
